body:
Hello, I'm new to Verilator and I'm working on Ubuntu 20.04.6 LTS with Verilator version 5.025. I'm trying to generate a VCD file, but I'm encountering an issue with the timescale(but the waveform is correct). Despite adding the option ```--timescale 1ns/1ns``` or including `timescale 1ns/1ns in my Verilog file header, the timescale remains at 1s. The option seems not work?
Here is my testbench to generate a VCD file:
```
#include <verilated.h>
#include <verilated_vcd_c.h>
#include "Vtop_tb.h"
 
int main(int argc, char** argv){
	
	VerilatedContext* contextp = new VerilatedContext;
	VerilatedVcdC* trace = new VerilatedVcdC;
	Vtop_tb* top = new Vtop_tb;

	contextp->traceEverOn(true);
	top->trace(trace,3);	
	trace->open("Vtop_tb.vcd");
	
	while (!contextp->gotFinish()){
		top->eval();
		trace->dump(contextp->time());
		contextp->timeInc(1);
	}

	trace->close();
	delete top;
	return 0;
}
```
I've also tried modifying sim_main.cpp in the /example/make_tracing_c file with the same logic as the testbench code mentioned earlier to generate a VCD file. However, I'm encountering the same issue with the timescale.
```
